# UI Consistency Defaults

Follow existing project UI patterns before introducing new styles.

- Use typography tokens and inherited sizing/weights:
  - body: `var(--ui-weight)`
  - emphasis/headings: `var(--ui-weight-strong)`
- Match nearby control density (font sizes, spacing, border radii) in the same tab/section.
- Prefer existing classes (`btn-muted`, preference row patterns, panel styles) over creating one-off variants.
- Avoid inline typography styles (`font-size`, `font-weight`, `line-height`) unless there is a documented one-off reason.
- Keep text-entry controls aligned with the project input baseline (12px, body weight, input tokens) including special fields like hex inputs.
- Use CSS variables for colors and borders; avoid hardcoded values unless explicitly required.
- Keep UI compact and subtle per `STYLE_GUIDE.md`.

Before shipping UI edits:

1. Compare new controls against neighboring controls in the same panel.
2. Confirm text sizing and weight match existing section conventions.
3. Confirm accent usage indicates state, not decoration.
